Package: AnomalyPheno
Title: Unsupervised Anomaly Phenotyping for Time Series via Topological Data Analysis
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Tony", "Lu", email = "xulunt123@gmail.com",
    role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description:
    Introduces the concept of "anomaly phenotyping" for univariate time
    series. The framework not only detects anomalies but automatically
    classifies them into interpretable, reproducible types (phenotypes).
    The pipeline operates in four layers: (1) detection of anomaly intervals
    via Spectral Residual (Ren et al., 2019
    <doi:10.1145/3292500.3330680>) or Local Outlier Factor sliding-window
    engine; (2) 27-dimensional multi-domain feature extraction covering
    morphological, spectral, temporal context, relative severity, and
    complexity domains (approximate entropy, Hurst exponent, turning-point
    rate, trend slope, zero-crossing rate); (3) Multi-Resolution Mapper
    topological clustering (Singh et al., 2007) run at three resolution
    scales with majority-vote aggregation and instance-level stability
    scores; and (4) automated phenotype characterisation including canonical
    templates, severity classification, phenotype confidence scores, and a
    feature importance ranking. Additional functions support external
    validation against ground-truth labels (Adjusted Rand Index, purity,
    per-phenotype F1), bootstrap stability analysis (Jaccard similarity
    across resamples), prospective classification of new anomaly segments,
    and cross-series phenotype comparison (Bhattacharyya similarity).
    A benchmark dataset with three known phenotype classes is included.
